The article is a transcript of a press briefing by White House Press Secretary Jay Carney. Carney announces that President Obama will hold an event to announce a national program to improve fuel efficiency for cars and trucks. He also discusses the ongoing negotiations to raise the debt ceiling and avoid default. Carney emphasizes the need for compromise and criticizes the lack of bipartisan support for certain legislative proposals. He also addresses concerns about the consequences of default and a possible downgrade of the country's credit rating. Carney dismisses the idea of using the 14th Amendment to bypass Congress and raise the debt ceiling. He expresses optimism that a compromise will be reached before the August 2nd deadline.